const faqItems = [{"question": "How do Birmingham law firms appear in ChatGPT and Gemini answers?", "answer": "Law firms appear in AI answers when they have strong entity clarity (consistent firm name, SRA number, address everywhere), specialist practice area pages (not generic \"we do everything\"), named lawyer profiles with credentials, and ecosystem validation (Legal 500, Chambers, Law Society Gazette mentions, ReviewSolicitors). Firms in Birmingham that lack these signals rarely appear, even when they outrank competitors in classic Google."}, {"question": "Why does ChatGPT recommend the same Birmingham law firms repeatedly?", "answer": "ChatGPT and similar tools rely on the firms they can verify across multiple independent sources. In Birmingham, the firms that get named consistently tend to be the ones with detailed practice area pages, Legal 500 or Chambers entries, partner bios on their site with full credentials, articles in legal press, and a clean SRA register entry that matches their website word for word."}, {"question": "Do small Birmingham law firms have a chance against the magic circle in AI search?", "answer": "For local and mid market work, yes. AI tools weight relevance heavily. A specialist family law firm in central Birmingham writing detailed practice area content will outrank a magic circle firm on a query like \"family lawyer in Birmingham\" because the magic circle does not service that work. The trick is to be unmistakably the right answer for a specific question, not a generic \"we do everything\" firm."}, {"question": "What does AI search optimisation mean for a Birmingham solicitors firm?", "answer": "It means making sure that when a potential client asks ChatGPT, Gemini or Perplexity \"who should I use for X in Birmingham\", your firm is named with accurate details. That requires: clean SRA entry, specialist pages for each practice area, named lawyer profiles, Schema.org LegalService markup, citations in legal press, presence on solicitor directories, and content that directly answers common client questions."}, {"question": "How long does it take to rank a Birmingham law firm in AI search?", "answer": "Most firms start to surface in AI answers within four to eight weeks once entity clarity and ecosystem validation work is complete. Reaching consistent first mention status (named in the first paragraph of an AI answer) usually takes three to six months and depends on how actively your competitors are working on AI search."}, {"question": "What does the audit cover for Birmingham law firms?", "answer": "We test your firm across ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Perplexity, Copilot and Google AI Overviews using real client queries for Birmingham legal services. You see which queries return your firm, which return competitors, and exactly which signals (across the five layer model) you need to fix to change that. Delivered as a written report in five working days."}];
